---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Free Web Development Tools - The Complete Guide 2024"
  description="Discover the best free web development tools to build modern websites and applications. Complete guide with downloadable resources."
>
  <Header slot="header" />
  <main>
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
      <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Free Web Development Tools: The Complete Guide 2024
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
          Build amazing websites and applications with these professional-grade free tools
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
          <span>Published on December 15, 2024</span>
          <span>â€¢</span>
          <span>8 min read</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Web development has never been more accessible, thanks to an incredible ecosystem of free tools that rival expensive commercial alternatives. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced developer, these tools will help you build modern, professional websites and applications without breaking the bank.
        </p>

        <h2>Code Editors & IDEs</h2>
        
        <h3>Visual Studio Code</h3>
        <p>
          Microsoft's Visual Studio Code is arguably the most popular code editor among developers today. It's completely free, open-source, and packed with features that make coding a pleasure.
        </p>

        <h3>Atom</h3>
        <p>
          GitHub's Atom editor offers a hackable text editor for the 21st century. While development has slowed, it remains a solid choice for many developers.
        </p>

        <h2>Version Control</h2>
        
        <h3>Git</h3>
        <p>
          Git is the industry-standard version control system. It's free, distributed, and essential for any serious development work.
        </p>

        <h3>GitHub</h3>
        <p>
          GitHub provides free hosting for Git repositories, along with powerful collaboration tools, issue tracking, and project management features.
        </p>

        <h2>Design Tools</h2>
        
        <h3>Figma</h3>
        <p>
          Figma revolutionized web design with its browser-based interface and real-time collaboration features. The free tier is generous enough for most personal projects.
        </p>

        <h3>GIMP</h3>
        <p>
          The GNU Image Manipulation Program is a powerful, free alternative to Photoshop for image editing and creation.
        </p>

        <h2>Development Frameworks</h2>
        
        <h3>React</h3>
        <p>
          Facebook's React library has become the go-to choice for building user interfaces. It's completely free and has a massive ecosystem of supporting tools.
        </p>

        <h3>Vue.js</h3>
        <p>
          Vue.js offers a progressive framework for building user interfaces. It's approachable for beginners yet powerful enough for complex applications.
        </p>

        <h2>Testing Tools</h2>
        
        <h3>Jest</h3>
        <p>
          Jest is a delightful JavaScript testing framework with a focus on simplicity. It works out of the box for most JavaScript projects.
        </p>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>
          The web development landscape is rich with free, high-quality tools that can help you build anything from simple websites to complex applications. Start with the basics like VS Code and Git, then gradually add more specialized tools as your projects grow in complexity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Ready to start coding?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-800 mb-4">Download these free tools and start building your next project today!</p>
        <a 
          href="/" 
          class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors"
        >
          Explore More Tools
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
